The paper deals with combinatorial optimization problems, specifically the graph 3-coloring problem, which is a well-known problem in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also mentions that the problem is NP-complete, which falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The algorithm proposed in the paper involves graph theory and computational geometry, which are both relevant to the sub-categories of computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses experimental analyses and probability, which are related to the sub-category of game theory (cs.GT).
